christiesinc인증됨'October 1949 (Rangitane)' is one of two large concave panels that Ben Nicholson was commissioned to create in 1949 for the New Zealand Shipping Company's newest steamship, the M.V. Rangitane. 🚢⠀⠀The present work wonderfully demonstrates Nicholson's mastery of composition and colour as well as his love of geometric simplicity. ⠀⠀Using a series of dynamic overlapping forms and interlocking planes he plays with notions of light and space, exploring the interplay between the representational and the abstract. ⠀⠀Ben Nicholson (1894-1982), 'October 1949 (Rangitane)' (1949). Estimate: £700,000 – £1,000,000.⠀⠀Modern British and Irish Art Evening Sale: 22 March, Live Auction 6.30PM GMT.⠀⠀#painting #art #artwork #artist #BenNicholson #modernbritishart⠀⠀32분
